t=\"17\" /></a></span><a href=\"/w/Champion%27s_lamp\" title=\"Champion&#39;s lamp\">Champion's lamp</a></li>\n<li><span class=\"plink-template\"><a href=\"/w/Champion%27s_cape\" title=\"Champion&#39;s cape\"><img alt=\"Champion&#39;s cape.png\" src=\"/images/Champion%27s_cape.png?3caf6\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"21\" height=\"29\" data-file-width=\"21\" data-file-height=\"29\" /></a></span><a href=\"/w/Champion%27s_cape\" title=\"Champion&#39;s cape\">Champion's cape</a></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mediawiki‐67df7655d‐sm4lh\nCached time: 20220420191440\nCache expiry: 86400\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: []\n[SMW] In‐text annotation parser time: 0 seconds\nCPU time usage: 0.106 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.129 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 733/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 17584/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 2856/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/100\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 2167/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.021/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 1126821/367001600 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   65.757      1 -total\n 29.59%   19.457      1 Template:Champions\n 23.65%   15.551      3 Template:CiteTwitter\n 20.97%   13.788      1 Template:External\n 19.53%   12.840      1 Template:Navbox\n  8.24%    5.420      1 Template:Reflist\n  7.98%    5.247      2 Template:Subject_changes\n  7.08%    4.656      1 Template:Ctg\n  6.21%    4.085     24 Template:Plink\n  2.84%    1.866      2 Template:Chatl\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key en_osrswiki:pcache:idhash:28395-0!canonical and timestamp 20220420191440 and revision id 14271566. Serialized with PHP.\n -->\n</div>","rawContent":"{{External|rs}}\n'''Champion's scrolls''' are scrolls that players can obtain when killing certain monsters. It is a challenge from that creature's race champion, and by taking the scroll to the cellar of the [[Champions' Guild]], they may be fought in the [[Champion's Challenge]] [[minigame]]. Each scroll is an extremely rare (1 in 5,000) drop from monsters of each race. When one is received as a drop, the message, \"''A Champion's scroll falls to the ground as you slay your opponent,\"'' appears. In order to be eligible to receive any Champion's scroll, players must have 32 [[quest points]] and be on a [[members]] world.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1084801603281002496|date=14 January 2019|archiveurl=https://archive.is/9KMB5|archivedate=26 May 2020|quote=The Champions Challenge? You need 32+ QP, and to be on a members' world.}}\n\nEvery champion has certain rules that the battle is fought under. These are outlined on the scroll. After winning the battle with the champion, players will get a small amount of [[experience]] in [[Hitpoints]] and [[Slayer]] [[skill]]s, and you cannot obtain another champion's scroll of that type again.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1118793092440764416|date=18 April 2019|archiveurl=https://archive.is/K97dq|archivedate=26 May 2020|quote=If you've killed a specific champion, the game no longer drops its challenge scroll for you.}} Although you cannot receive the Champion's scroll after completing the challenge, it is possible to roll the drop again in which case you will receive the message \"''You have a funny feeling you would have received a Champion's scroll...''\".{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1471450361030483973|date=16 December 2021|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/LZanp|archivedate=8 April 2022|quote=Yes, we added a message if you roll the random number but don't receive a scroll because you'd already done the challenge. Someone suggested they'd like to know, so their clan could use it for bingo.}}\n\nThere are 10 different champion scrolls, each from a different race's champion, plus 1 champion scroll from champion of champions, human race champion [[Leon D'Cour]], who can only be fought after beating all other champions. When every champion has been slain, you may claim the [[Champion's cape]] from [[Larxus]].\n\nA champion's scroll is needed for the [[music cape]], as the soundtrack \"[[Victory is Mine]]\" is unlocked in the arena.\n\n==Scrolls==\n{| class=\"wikitable lighttable\"\n! Scroll !! Dropping [[monster]] ([[Combat level|level]]) !! Champion ([[Combat level|level]])\n|-\n| {{plink|Imp champion scroll|txt=Imp}} || [[Imp]] (2, 7) || [[Imp Champion]] (14)\n|-\n| {{plink|Goblin champion scroll|txt=Goblin}} || [[Goblin]] (2-13) || [[Goblin Champion]] (24)\n|-\n| {{plink|Skeleton champion scroll|txt=Skeleton}} || [[Skeleton]] (13-142) || [[Skeleton Champion]] (40)\n|-\n| {{plink|Zombie champion scroll|txt=Zombie}} || [[Zombie]] (13-100) || [[Zombies Champion]] (51)\n|-\n| {{plink|Giant champion scroll|txt=Giant}} ||[[Hill giant]] (28), [[Fire Giant]], [[Moss Giant]], [[Ice giant]]||[[Giant Champion]] (56)\n|-\n| {{plink|Hobgoblin champion scroll|txt=Hobgoblin}} ||[[Hobgoblin]] (28, 42) || [[Hobgoblin Champion]] (56)\n|-\n| {{plink|Ghoul champion scroll|txt=Ghoul}}||[[Ghoul]] (42) || [[Ghoul Champion]] (85)\n|-\n| {{plink|Earth warrior champion scroll|txt=Earth warrior}} ||[[Earth warrior]] (51) || [[Earth Warrior Champion]] (102)\n|-\n| {{plink|Jogre champion scroll|txt=Jogre}} ||[[Jogre]] (53) || [[Jogre Champion]] (107)\n|-\n| {{plink|Lesser demon champion scroll|txt=Lesser demon}} ||[[Lesser demon]] (82, 87, 94) ||[[Lesser Demon Champion]] (162)\n|-\n| {{plink|Leon's champion scroll|txt=Human}} || [[Unobtainable items|Unobtainable]] || [[Leon d'Cour]] (141)\n|}\n\n==Changes==\n{{Subject changes header}}\n{{Subject changes\n|date = 16 December 2021\n|update = Christmas 2021\n|poll = \n|change = If a Champion's scroll would have dropped as a duplicate, the game message \"''{{Colour|#990000|You have a funny feeling that you would have received a Champion's scroll...}}''\" appears now.\n}}\n{{Subject changes\n|date = 25 June 2015\n|update = Boss Room Counters & Platinum Tokens\n|poll = Old School Content Poll 34: XP droplets & Slayer\n|change = Players will now receive a coloured message in their chat box upon receiving a champion scroll drop.\n}}\n{{Subject changes footer}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Champions}}"}